
                                            The African National Congress announced its top six in Nasrec on Monday. Twitter users reacted with differing opinions to the new leadership. 
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Twitter users countrywide have reacted with differing opinions to the newly elected African National Congress (ANC) top six. Cyril Ramaphosa has been announced as ANC president, his deputy is David Mabuza, chairperson of the party is Gwede Mantashe, secretary-general went to Ace Magashule; deputy secretary-general is Jessie Duarte  and finally, the treasurer general of the party is Paul Mashatile. Users waited with bated breath as the announcement was delayed.     When the results were finally announced, people reacted with jubilation, disappointment and some humour:               